  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Study hypothesis: umbilical cord drainage of fetal blood after delivery of the infant would
      reduce the incidence of feto-maternal transfusion. Patients were randomized to placental
      drainage or no drainage at the time of cesarean section. The incidence of fetal to maternal
      transfusion was noted postoperatively.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      86 patients were randomized to placental drainage vs. no drainage of fetal blood at the time
      of cesarean section. Kleihauer-Betke testing was performed within 12 hours postoperatively to
      assess the incidence of feto-maternal transfusion. A significant difference was found between
      the two groups.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
